<h1>Yet Another Perl Conference</h1>
</center>

The Yet Another Perl Conferences (YAPCs) are grassroots symposia on the Perl programming language under the auspices of the <a href="http://yetanother.org/">Yet Another Society</a> (<a href="http://yetanother.org/">YAS</a>), a non-profit corporation for the advancement of collaborative efforts in computer and information sciences.
<hr>
<h2>Information on Upcoming Events</h2>

<h3>YAPC::Asia 2006 in Tokyo</h3>

<p><a href="http://tokyo.yapcasia.org/blog/">YAPC::Asia</a> will be in Tokyo March 29 - 30, 2006. They are currently accepting talks and it looks like the talks will be in English and Japanese.</p>

<h3>Open Source Developers' Conference in Israel</h3>
<p>
<a href="http://www.perl.org.il/YAPC/">YAPC::Israel</a> has morphed into the Open Source Developers' Conference. <a href="http://www.osdc.org.il/">OSDC Israel</a> is scheduled for February 26-28, 2006 in Netanya, Israel. There will also be a <a href="http://www.pugscode.org/">Pugs</a> <a href="http://www.osdc.org.il/hackathon.html">hack-a-thon</a> before the conference.
</p>

<h3>YAPC::NA::2006 Venue Selected and Dates Released</h3>                                                                    
<p>
Chicago was recently selected to <a href="http://yapc.org/America/">YAPC::NA 2006</a>. The conference will be held on June 26<sup>th</sup>-28<sup>th</sup> on the campus of the Illinois Institute of Technology.
</p>

<h3>YAPC::Europe::2006 in Birmingham, UK</h3>
<p>
YAPC::Europe::2006 will be in Birmingham, UK with the theme <i>The Accessibility of Perl</i>.
</p>
<hr>
<h2>Other News</h2>

<h3>London Perl Workshop</h3>
<p>
The <a href="http://london.pm.org/lpw/index.html">London Perl Workshop</a> is a free one-day conference in central London, UK. It was held most recently on Saturday, November 26, 2005. Details on the talks are available at the <a href="http://london.pm.org/lpw/index.html">London Perl Workshop</a> website.
</p>

<h3>YAPC::NA::2005 Conference Proceedings Available</h3>
<p>
You can now re-live the excitement from YAPC::NA::2005 because the Toronto Perl Mongers have announced the availability of the proceedings from YAPC::NA::2005 held in Toronto. You can find <a href="http://use.perl.org/article.pl?sid=05/11/23/0320248&tid=1&tid=43">details on how to get the proceedings</a> at <a href="http://use.perl.org">use.perl.org</a>.
<p>
